From the definitions of $a, b$ and $c$, we see that \begin{align*}\frac{ac+b^2}{ab} &= \frac{(-1+i) + (1-i)^2}{1-i} \\ &=\frac{-1+i+2i+1}{1-i} \\ &= \frac{3i}{1-i} \\ &= \frac{3i(1+i)}{(1-i)(1+i)} \\ &= -\frac{3}{2} + \frac{3}{2}i \\ \end{align*} Therefore the answer is $-\frac{3}{2}+\frac{3}{2}i$. \end{think}

